Omnichannel Inventory Data Mappings

The Omnichannel Inventory connector maps the data source objects to the data model objects (DMO) and establishes DMO relationships.

The Omnichannel Inventory connecter creates these data streams in the Data Stream workspace in Data Cloud using this format.

LocationGroupExclusion_[Omnichannel Inventory org name]
LocationInventory_[Omnichannel Inventory org name]
GroupInventory_[Omnichannel Inventory org name]

Don’t remove these data streams. Removing them breaks the Omnichannel Inventory connection.

This table lists information about the source objects.

SOURCE OBJECT	DESCRIPTION	MAPPING REFERENCE
Location Group Product Exclusion Change	Represents a change to the Location Group Product Exclusion list.	Location Group Product Exclusion Change Mapping
Location Product Inventory Change	Represents a change to product inventory at a location.	Location Product Inventory Change Mapping
Location Group Product Inventory Change	Represents a change to product inventory at a location group.	Location Group Product Inventory Change Mapping
